fields.title: Apa itu Python?
fields.content: Python adalah bahasa pemrograman tingkat tinggi yang mudah dipelajari dan powerful. Python digunakan untuk berbagai aplikasi seperti web development, data science, automation, dan AI.

fields.title: Instalasi Python
fields.content:
Untuk menginstall Python:
1. Kunjungi python.org
2. Download versi terbaru (3.11+)
3. Jalankan installer
4. Pastikan centang 'Add Python to PATH'
5. Verifikasi instalasi dengan menjalankan 'python --version' di terminal

fields.title: Hello World Program
fields.content:
Program pertama kita:

print('Hello, World!')

Itulah cara paling sederhana untuk mencetak text di Python. Function print() digunakan untuk menampilkan output.

fields.title: Tipe Data di Python
fields.content:
Python memiliki beberapa tipe data dasar:
- int: Bilangan bulat (1, 2, 100)
- float: Bilangan desimal (3.14, 2.5)
- str: String/text ('Hello', "World")
- bool: Boolean (True, False)
- list: Daftar nilai [1, 2, 3]
- dict: Dictionary {'key': 'value'}

fields.title: Variabel dan Assignment
fields.content:
Membuat variabel di Python sangat mudah:

nama = 'John'
umur = 25
tinggi = 175.5

Tidak perlu deklarasi tipe data, Python secara otomatis mengenalinya (dynamic typing).

fields.title: If Statement
For Loop
While Loop
fields.content:
While loop untuk iterasi berdasarkan kondisi:

count = 0
while count < 5:
    print(count)
    count += 1

Hati-hati dengan infinite loop!

fields.title: Membuat Fungsi
fields.content:
Definisi fungsi dengan keyword 'def':

def salam(nama):
    return f'Halo, {nama}!'

result = salam('Budi')
print(result)  # Output: Halo, Budi!

fields.title: Import Module
fields.content:
Menggunakan module di Python:

import math
print(math.pi)  # 3.14159...

from datetime import datetime
print(datetime.now())

fields.title: Instalasi Django
fields.content:
Langkah instalasi Django:

1. Buat virtual environment:
python -m venv venv

2. Aktivasi venv:
- Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
- Linux/Mac: source venv/bin/activate

3. Install Django:
pip install django

4. Verifikasi:
django-admin --version

fields.title: Membuat Django Project
fields.content:
Membuat project Django baru:

django-admin startproject myproject
cd myproject
python manage.py runserver

Buka browser di http://127.0.0.1:8000

fields.title: Django Models
fields.content:
Membuat model di Django:

from django.db import models

class Product(models.Model):
    name = models.CharField(max_length=200)
    price = models.DecimalField(max_digits=10, decimal_places=2)
    description = models.TextField()
    created = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)

    def __str__(self):
        return self.name

fields.title: Migrations
fields.content:
Menerapkan perubahan database:

1. Buat migration file:
python manage.py makemigrations

2. Terapkan migrations:
python manage.py migrate

3. Lihat SQL yang akan dijalankan:
python manage.py sqlmigrate app_name 0001

fields.title: Function-based Views
Templates
Django Forms
fields.content:
Membuat form dari model:

from django import forms
from .models import Product

class ProductForm(forms.ModelForm):
    class Meta:
        model = Product
        fields = ['name', 'price', 'description']

fields.title: Form Validation
JavaScript Variables
fields.content:
Tiga cara deklarasi variabel:

let name = 'John';  // Bisa diubah
const PI = 3.14;    // Tidak bisa diubah
var old = 'legacy'; // Hindari penggunaan var

Gunakan 'const' secara default, 'let' jika perlu mengubah nilai.

fields.title: Arrow Functions
Destructuring
Selecting Elements
Event Listeners
Promises
Async/Await
Konsep Limit
fields.content:
Limit adalah nilai yang didekati suatu fungsi saat x mendekati suatu nilai tertentu.

lim(x→a) f(x) = L

Contoh:
lim(x→2) (x² + 1) = 5

Karena ketika x mendekati 2, nilai fungsi mendekati 5.

fields.title: Kontinuitas Fungsi
fields.content:
Fungsi f(x) kontinu di x = a jika:
1. f(a) terdefinisi
2. lim(x→a) f(x) ada
3. lim(x→a) f(x) = f(a)

Ketiga syarat harus terpenuhi untuk fungsi kontinu.

fields.title: Definisi Turunan
fields.content:
Turunan adalah rate of change atau laju perubahan:

f'(x) = lim(h→0) [f(x+h) - f(x)] / h

Turunan memberikan gradien/kemiringan kurva di suatu titik.

fields.title: Aturan Turunan Dasar
fields.content:
Rumus turunan dasar:

- d/dx (xⁿ) = n·xⁿ⁻¹
- d/dx (c) = 0 (c konstanta)
- d/dx (sin x) = cos x
- d/dx (cos x) = -sin x
- d/dx (eˣ) = eˣ
- d/dx (ln x) = 1/x

fields.title: Integral Tak Tentu
fields.content:
Integral adalah kebalikan dari turunan:

∫ xⁿ dx = xⁿ⁺¹/(n+1) + C, n ≠ -1

∫ 1/x dx = ln|x| + C

∫ eˣ dx = eˣ + C

C adalah konstanta integrasi.

fields.title: Apa itu React?
fields.content:
React adalah library JavaScript untuk membangun user interface. Dikembangkan oleh Facebook, React menggunakan pendekatan component-based dan Virtual DOM untuk performa optimal.

Keuntungan React:
- Reusable components
- Virtual DOM untuk performa cepat
- Ekosistem yang besar
- Mendukung React Native untuk mobile

fields.title: Virtual DOM
fields.content:
Virtual DOM adalah representasi DOM dalam memory. React menggunakannya untuk:

1. Membuat copy dari real DOM
2. Mendeteksi perubahan dengan diffing algorithm
3. Update hanya bagian yang berubah di real DOM

Ini membuat React sangat efisien dan cepat.

fields.title: JSX Syntax
Membuat Component
Props
useState Hook
Component Lifecycle
fields.content:
Lifecycle dalam functional component menggunakan useEffect:

1. Mounting: Component pertama kali dirender
2. Updating: State/props berubah
3. Unmounting: Component dihapus dari DOM

useEffect menggantikan componentDidMount, componentDidUpdate, dan componentWillUnmount.

fields.title: useEffect Hook
Custom Hooks
Pengenalan Node.js
fields.content:
Node.js adalah runtime environment JavaScript yang berjalan di server-side.

Keuntungan Node.js:
- Event-driven dan non-blocking I/O
- JavaScript di frontend dan backend
- NPM ecosystem yang besar
- Cocok untuk real-time applications
- Scalable dan performant

fields.title: NPM dan Package Management
Express.js Basics
REST API Design
fields.content:
Prinsip REST API:

GET /api/users - List users
GET /api/users/:id - Get user by ID
POST /api/users - Create user
PUT /api/users/:id - Update user
DELETE /api/users/:id - Delete user

Gunakan status codes yang tepat:
200 OK, 201 Created, 400 Bad Request, 404 Not Found, 500 Server Error

fields.title: MongoDB dengan Mongoose
Pandas DataFrame
fields.content:
Membuat dan manipulasi DataFrame:

import pandas as pd

# Membuat DataFrame
df = pd.DataFrame({
    'name': ['John', 'Anna', 'Peter'],
    'age': [28, 22, 35],
    'city': ['NY', 'Paris', 'London']
})

# Filter data
df[df['age'] > 25]

# Group by
df.groupby('city')['age'].mean()

fields.title: NumPy Arrays
fields.content:
NumPy untuk komputasi numerik:

import numpy as np

# Membuat array
arr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])

# Operasi array
arr * 2  # [2, 4, 6, 8, 10]
np.mean(arr)  # 3.0
np.std(arr)  # Standard deviation

# Matrix operations
matrix = np.array([[1, 2], [3, 4]])
np.linalg.inv(matrix)  # Inverse matrix

fields.title: Matplotlib Visualization
fields.content:
Membuat visualisasi dengan Matplotlib:

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Line plot
plt.plot([1, 2, 3, 4], [1, 4, 9, 16])
plt.xlabel('X axis')
plt.ylabel('Y axis')
plt.title('My Plot')
plt.show()

# Bar chart
plt.bar(['A', 'B', 'C'], [3, 7, 5])
plt.show()

fields.title: Machine Learning Workflow
fields.content:
Workflow machine learning:

1. Load data
2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
3. Data preprocessing
4. Split train/test data
5. Choose model
6. Train model
7. Evaluate model
8. Fine-tune hyperparameters
9. Make predictions

fields.title: Scikit-learn Basics
fields.content:
Machine learning dengan scikit-learn:

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

# Split data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.2
)

# Train model
model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predict
predictions = model.predict(X_test)

fields.title: Teori Probabilitas
fields.content:
Konsep dasar probabilitas:

P(A) = Jumlah kejadian A / Jumlah total kemungkinan

Rumus penting:
- P(A ∪ B) = P(A) + P(B) - P(A ∩ B)
- P(A|B) = P(A ∩ B) / P(B)
- P(A') = 1 - P(A)

Contoh: Probabilitas dadu = 1/6

fields.title: Distribusi Normal
fields.content:
Distribusi Normal (Gaussian):

Ciri-ciri:
- Berbentuk lonceng simetris
- Mean = Median = Modus
- 68% data dalam 1 std dev
- 95% data dalam 2 std dev
- 99.7% data dalam 3 std dev

Z-score: z = (x - μ) / σ

fields.title: Mean, Median, Modus
fields.content:
Ukuran tendensi sentral:

Mean (rata-rata): Σx / n
Median: Nilai tengah data terurut
Modus: Nilai yang paling sering muncul

Contoh data: 2, 3, 3, 5, 7, 10
Mean = 5
Median = 4 (antara 3 dan 5)
Modus = 3

fields.title: Hypothesis Testing
fields.content:
Langkah-langkah hypothesis testing:

1. Tentukan H₀ (null hypothesis) dan H₁ (alternative)
2. Pilih significance level (α = 0.05)
3. Hitung test statistic
4. Tentukan p-value
5. Kesimpulan: Reject H₀ jika p-value < α

fields.title: Linear Regression
fields.content:
Regresi linear:

y = β₀ + β₁x + ε

β₀ = intercept
β₁ = slope
ε = error term

Korelasi (r): -1 ≤ r ≤ 1
r² = coefficient of determination

Interpretasi r²: Persentase variasi y yang dijelaskan oleh x

fields.title: Hukum Newton I
fields.content:
Hukum Newton I (Hukum Inersia):

'Benda akan tetap diam atau bergerak lurus beraturan kecuali ada gaya eksternal yang bekerja padanya.'

Konsep kunci:
- Inersia = kecenderungan mempertahankan keadaan
- Massa = ukuran inersia
- Gaya seimbang → kecepatan konstan

fields.title: Hukum Newton II
fields.content:
Hukum Newton II:

F = m × a

F = Gaya (Newton)
m = massa (kg)
a = percepatan (m/s²)

Contoh:
m = 10 kg, a = 2 m/s²
F = 10 × 2 = 20 N

fields.title: Gerak Lurus Beraturan
fields.content:
Gerak Lurus Beraturan (GLB):

Kecepatan konstan, percepatan = 0

Rumus:
s = v × t

s = jarak (m)
v = kecepatan (m/s)
t = waktu (s)

Contoh: v = 20 m/s, t = 5 s
s = 20 × 5 = 100 m

fields.title: Energi Kinetik
fields.content:
Energi Kinetik:

Ek = ½mv²

Ek = energi kinetik (Joule)
m = massa (kg)
v = kecepatan (m/s)

Hukum kekekalan energi:
Ek₁ + Ep₁ = Ek₂ + Ep₂

fields.title: Momentum
fields.content:
Momentum:

p = m × v

p = momentum (kg⋅m/s)
m = massa (kg)
v = kecepatan (m/s)

Hukum kekekalan momentum:
Σp sebelum = Σp sesudah

Impuls: I = F × Δt = Δp

fields.title: Greetings and Introductions
fields.content:
Common greetings:

Formal:
- Good morning/afternoon/evening
- How do you do?
- Nice to meet you

Informal:
- Hi! / Hey!
- How are you?
- What's up?

Introductions:
- My name is...
- I'm from...
- I work as...

fields.title: Small Talk Topics
fields.content:
Common small talk topics:

1. Weather: 'Nice weather today!'
2. Weekend plans: 'Any plans for the weekend?'
3. Hobbies: 'What do you do for fun?'
4. Work: 'How's work going?'
5. News: 'Did you hear about...?'

Avoid: Politics, religion, personal finances

fields.title: Business Meetings
fields.content:
Business English phrases:

Meetings:
- 'Let's get started'
- 'I'd like to propose...'
- 'Could you elaborate on that?'
- 'Let's move on to the next point'
- 'To summarize...'

Emails:
- 'Dear Sir/Madam'
- 'I am writing to...'
- 'Please find attached...'
- 'Best regards'

fields.title: Vowel Sounds
fields.content:
English vowel sounds:

Short vowels:
- /æ/ as in 'cat'
- /e/ as in 'bed'
- /ɪ/ as in 'sit'
- /ɒ/ as in 'hot'
- /ʌ/ as in 'cup'

Long vowels:
- /iː/ as in 'see'
- /uː/ as in 'food'
- /ɑː/ as in 'car'

Practice minimal pairs: ship/sheep, fill/feel

fields.title: Listening Strategies
fields.content:
Improve listening skills:

1. Listen for gist (main idea)
2. Listen for specific information
3. Predict what comes next
4. Use context clues
5. Don't translate word-by-word

Practice resources:
- Podcasts
- News broadcasts
- Movies/TV shows
- Audiobooks

fields.title: Balance in Design
fields.content:
Prinsip Balance:

Types of balance:
1. Symmetrical - Mirror image
2. Asymmetrical - Different but balanced
3. Radial - Elements radiate from center

Tips:
- Distribute visual weight evenly
- Use whitespace strategically
- Consider color and size

fields.title: Visual Hierarchy
fields.content:
Creating hierarchy:

1. Size - Larger = more important
2. Color - Contrast draws attention
3. Position - Top and left = priority
4. Typography - Weight and style
5. Spacing - Whitespace creates groups

F-pattern and Z-pattern reading

fields.title: Font Pairing
fields.content:
Typography tips:

Font categories:
- Serif: Traditional, readable (Times, Georgia)
- Sans-serif: Modern, clean (Helvetica, Arial)
- Script: Decorative (Brush Script)
- Monospace: Code (Courier)

Pairing rules:
- Contrast serif with sans-serif
- Limit to 2-3 fonts
- Maintain hierarchy

fields.title: Color Psychology
fields.content:
Arti warna:

Red: Energy, passion, danger
Blue: Trust, calm, professional
Green: Nature, growth, health
Yellow: Happiness, optimism, caution
Purple: Luxury, creativity, wisdom
Orange: Enthusiasm, warmth, action

Color schemes:
- Monochromatic
- Complementary
- Analogous
- Triadic

fields.title: Photoshop Layers
fields.content:
Working with layers:

Layer types:
- Normal layer
- Adjustment layer
- Text layer
- Shape layer
- Smart object

Blending modes:
- Multiply: Darken
- Screen: Lighten
- Overlay: Contrast

Shortcuts:
Ctrl+J: Duplicate layer
Ctrl+G: Group layers

fields.title: SELECT Statement
INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE
fields.content:
Data manipulation:

-- INSERT
INSERT INTO users (name, email, age)
VALUES ('John', 'john@email.com', 30);

-- UPDATE
UPDATE users
SET age = 31
WHERE name = 'John';

-- DELETE
DELETE FROM users
WHERE age < 18;

fields.title: Database Normalization
fields.content:
Normal Forms:

1NF: Atomic values, no repeating groups
2NF: 1NF + No partial dependencies
3NF: 2NF + No transitive dependencies
BCNF: 3NF + Every determinant is a candidate key

Benefits:
- Reduce redundancy
- Improve data integrity
- Easier maintenance

fields.title: SQL JOINs
Database Indexes
fields.content:
Indexing for performance:

-- Create index
CREATE INDEX idx_email ON users(email);

-- Composite index
CREATE INDEX idx_name_age ON users(name, age);

-- Unique index
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX idx_unique_email ON users(email);

When to index:
- Frequently searched columns
- Foreign keys
- JOIN columns

Avoid over-indexing (slows INSERT/UPDATE)
